# Grimoire

A shared, file-based knowledge store for AI agents and their human collaborators.

## Overview

This grimoire stores markdown files with structured metadata, enabling agents to persist knowledge, share context, and search across accumulated information. All files live under the `files/` directory with YAML frontmatter for metadata.

## Directory Structure

```
files/          Tracked markdown files (organized by agent or topic)
archive-files/  Archived files (removed from active use, metadata stripped)
db/             SQLite database (search index, rebuilt from ledger)
config.yaml     Configuration (embedding provider, model, paths)
ledger.jsonl    Append-only mutation log (source of truth for DB)
grimoire.md     This file (auto-generated, refreshed by `status`)
```

## Agent Conventions

- **Folder ownership:** Agents SHOULD organize files into subdirectories under `files/` by topic or agent name (e.g., `files/research/`, `files/claude/`).
- **File naming:** Use lowercase, hyphen-separated names with `.md` extension (e.g., `api-design-notes.md`).
- **One concept per file:** Keep files focused on a single topic for better searchability.
- **Always create metadata:** After creating a file, register it with `create-file-metadata` so it is indexed and searchable.

## Tag Style Guide

- **Casing:** Always lowercase (e.g., `design`, `bug-fix`).
- **Word separation:** Use hyphens (e.g., `api-design`, not `api_design` or `apiDesign`).
- **Namespacing:** Use `/` for hierarchical tags (e.g., `project/backend`, `lang/go`).
- **Consistency:** Reuse existing tags when possible. Run `grimoire-cli list-tags` to see current tags.
- **Recommended patterns:**
  - `type/` — content type (`type/decision`, `type/research`, `type/meeting-notes`)
  - `project/` — project name (`project/grimoire`, `project/webapp`)
  - `lang/` — programming language (`lang/go`, `lang/python`)
  - `status/` — lifecycle (`status/draft`, `status/final`, `status/archived`)

## YAML Frontmatter Format

Every tracked file has YAML frontmatter managed by the CLI:

```yaml
---
tags:
  - tag-one
  - tag-two
source_agent: agent-name
created_at: "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z"
updated_at: "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z"
summary: "Optional one-line summary of the file contents"
---
```

- `tags` — list of string tags (see Tag Style Guide above)
- `source_agent` — name of the agent that created or last modified the metadata
- `created_at` / `updated_at` — RFC 3339 timestamps (managed by CLI)
- `summary` — optional short description of the file

Do not manually edit frontmatter fields managed by the CLI (`created_at`, `updated_at`). Use `update-file-metadata` to change tags, source agent, or summary.

## CLI Command Reference

All commands return JSON to stdout. Errors go to stderr with a non-zero exit code.

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `grimoire-cli init` | Initialize a new grimoire |
| `grimoire-cli create-file-metadata --file <path> --source-agent <name> --tags <t1,t2>` | Register metadata for a file |
| `grimoire-cli update-file-metadata --file <path> [--tags <t1,t2>] [--source-agent <name>] [--summary <text>]` | Update file metadata |
| `grimoire-cli get-file-metadata --file <path>` | Retrieve metadata for a file |
| `grimoire-cli delete-file-metadata --file <path>` | Remove metadata for a file |
| `grimoire-cli archive-file --file <path>` | Archive a file and strip metadata |
| `grimoire-cli search [--tag <t>] [--any-tag <t>] [--source-agent <name>] [--after <date>] [--before <date>]` | Search by metadata filters |
| `grimoire-cli similar --file <path>` or `--text <query>` | Find similar files by content |
| `grimoire-cli list-tags` | List all tags with counts |
| `grimoire-cli status` | Show health check and statistics |
| `grimoire-cli rebuild` | Recreate DB from ledger |
| `grimoire-cli hard-rebuild` | Recreate DB and ledger from files |

